{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs are trained on large, static datasets that may not always contain the most recent or specialized medical knowledge.",
    "Due to limited access to key sources like PubMed or Google Scholar, training data may lack essential medical information [144].",
    "This shortcoming may lead to superficial knowledge of complex orthopedic concepts.",
    "As the field of medicine is continuously evolving, the inability of generative AI tools to update in real time with new information is a significant Fig. 3 Challenges and potential solutions associated with integrating generative AI into orthopaedic education.",
    "Key challenges include algorithmic bias, inaccuracies, inconsistent outputs, overreliance on AI, academic dishonesty, and privacy concerns."
  ]
}